'''Chancellor''' was a [[Politics|political]] position in different governments in which the individual was tasked with representing or leading the government. There were different chancellery positions that were similar however, such as the [[Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic]], [[Chancellor (Rebel Alliance)|Chancellor]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]], and the [[Chancellor (New Republic)|Chancellor]] of the [[New Republic]].

==Description==
The position of chancellor was given to an individual to lead or represent a government or parts of a government.<ref name="Darth Vader 17" /> Similar chancellery positions existed, such as the [[Supreme Chancellor]] who was the supreme executive of the [[Galactic Republic]].<ref name="Episode II">{{Film|II}}</ref> Later, there also existed the [[Chancellor (Rebel Alliance)|Chancellor]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]]<ref name="Star Wars 4">[[Star Wars (2015) 4|''Star Wars'' (2015) 4]]</ref> which served as Chief of State<ref name="Rogue One VD">''[[Star Wars: Rogue One: The Ultimate Visual Guide]]''</ref> and later the [[Chancellor (New Republic)|Chancellor]] of the [[New Republic]] who had little power and was not considered an executive.<ref name="Bloodline">[[Bloodline (novel)|''Bloodline'']]</ref>

==History==
[[Contispex I]] was an individual that served as a Chancellor and died by the [[Standard year|year]] [[10 BBY]] as their ashes were held in an ark on the ''[[First Light]]'', the personal [[Yacht|star yacht]] of [[Crimson Dawn]] [[crime lord]] [[Dryden Vos]].<ref name="Solo Guide">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story The Official Guide]]''</ref>

[[Chamberlain]] [[Jooli]] of the [[Kingdom of Shu-Torun]] held the position of chancellor for approximately four [[Standard decade|decades]] until the [[death]] of the [[Unidentified King of Shu-Torun|King of Shu-Torun]] in the [[Standard year|year]] [[0 ABY]].<ref name="Darth Vader 18" /> Retaining the chancellery under [[Queen]] [[Trios]], the late [[king]]'s sole-surviving heir, Jooli became an [[advisor]] to the new [[Monarch of Shu-Torun|monarch]] during the [[Shu-Torun War|civil war]] between the royalty and the rebellious [[ore-duke]]s led by [[Duke]] [[Rubix]].<ref name="Darth Vader 17" /> Prior to the [[Battle at Rubix's citadel|final battle]] of the war, Jooli attempted to countermand Trios' decision to attack [[Rubix's delving citadel]] without the [[Galactic Empire]]'s [[Imperial Military|military support]], asserting his authority to do so by using the traditional advisory veto of his position. Trios reacted by accusing him of [[treason]] and consequently ordered her loyalist [[soldier]]s to execute the chancellor.<ref name="Darth Vader 18" />

After the [[Battle of Endor]] during the Galactic Civil War, [[Asera]] served as the chancellor of [[Rekkana]], but was subjugated by the Galactic Empire. Rekkana was eventually liberated by the [[New Republic]].<ref name="Hare-Brained Heist">{{IDWAdventuresCite-2017|annual=2019|story=Hare-Brained Heist}}</ref> During the [[First Order-Resistance War|war]] between the [[First Order]] and the [[Resistance]], the [[Ryloth government|planetary government of Ryloth]] was led by Chancellor [[Drelomon]].<ref name="Resistance Reborn" />

